@Node TNG7 "STCCG.guide/Episodes/TNG/Lonely Among Us"

  @{b}Lonely Among Us@{ub}

The crew of the Enterprise is faced with more threats than they realize while
transporting two parties of rival alien races to a peace summit which they
seem to busy trying to kill each other to prepare for, but the greater danger
lies in a consciousness which, after being swept into the sensor arrays of
the ship, is trying to escape the ship to return to its home. In its final
attempt, it beams off the Enterprise, taking Picard with it.


Cards from this episode:

  @{"Diplomatic Conference" link "XXPATH:mission.guide/DIPLCONFERENCE"}

@Endnode

@Node TNG8 "STCCG.guide/Episodes/TNG/Justice"

  @{b}Justice@{ub}

When Wesley unknowingly breaks a law of the Edo - a peacful race living on
Rubicon III - Picard must choose between violating the prime Directive and
allowing the boy to endure the only punishment prescribed by Edo tradition:
Death.


