@Node TNG12 "STCCG.guide/Episodes/TNG/The Big Good-Bye"

  @{b}The Big Good-Bye@{ub}

After completing a grueling preparation for contact with the protocol-sensitive
Jarada, Picard joins Crusher, Data and fiction expert Whalen for a relaxing
holodeck adventure based on Dixon Hill - a fictional detective of the 1940s.
Unfortunately a sensor probe from the Jarade damages the holodeck and en-
dangers their lives.


Cards from this episode:

  @{"Dixon Hill's Business Card" link "XXPATH:interrupt.guide/DIXONHILLCARD"}

@Endnode

@Node TNG13 "STCCG.guide/Episodes/TNG/Data Lore"

  @{b}Data Lore@{ub}

On Omicron Theta an away team finds a complete set of parts for an android.
After reassambly the android introduces himself as Lore, Data's brother.
Barely in time, Data and Wesley discover Lore's evil intent to feed the
crew to a malevolent creature called the crstalline entity.


Cards from this episode:

  @{"Hidden Entrance" link "XXPATH:dilemma.guide/HDDENTR"}
  @{"Off Switch" link "XXPATH:interrupt.guide/OFFSWITCH"}

@Endnode

@Node TNG14 "STCCG.guide/Episodes/TNG/Angel One"

  @{b}Angel One@{ub}

Beaming down to the planet Angel One to recover the crew of the disabled
freighter Odin, Riker and an away team discover that the men do not wish
to leave, even though their lives are in danger because their presence
is upsetting the heavily matriarchal culture.


Cards from this episode:

  @{"Matriarchal Society" link "XXPATH:dilemma.guide/MATSOC"}

@Endnode

@Node TNG15 "STCCG.guide/Episodes/TNG/11001001"

  @{b}11001001@{ub}

The Enterprise, while docked at a Starbase for minor refits, is hijacked
by the Bynars, whose home star has gone nova, rendering their computerized
planet inoperative. They have stored the contents of their race's memory
in the ship's computer in the hopes that Riker and Picard - being stalled
in the holodeck by the beautiful woman of Riker's dreams - can reactivate
their home.


