@Node TNG75 "STCCG.guide/Episodes/TNG/The Best of Both Worlds, Part II"

  @{b}The Best of Both Worlds, Part II@{ub}

The main deflector dish has no effect on the Borg because, having assimilated
Picard and converted him into their spokesman, Locutus, the Borg know now
every strategy and contigency that Picard hd been informed of before his
kidnapping. Riker is promoted to Captain by Admiral Hanson, who then leads a
fleet of 40 starships to Wolf 359 to confront the Borg, but the fleet's
efforts are in vain - every starship is annihilated. Riker orders a cunning
attack consisting of awkward strategies that Picard would never have carried
out or expected, and an away team kidnaps Locutus and returns him to the
Enterprise. Data then links up to Locutus to access the Borg communication
network, but every approach he takes to disarm the Borg down fails until the
Borg arrive at Earth to begin their domination of the Federation. Data triggers
the Borg regeneration process, putting every Borg to "sleep", but this also
triggers the self-destruction of the Borg ship. Picard is freed from the Borg,
Shelby returns to Starfleet to rebuild the fleet, and Rikere remains on the
Enterprise to continue serving as first officer. However, staring out the
window of his ready room, Picard's face indicated that all is not well...


