@Node TNG131 "STCCG.guide/Episodes/TNG/Schisms"

  @{b}Schisms@{ub}

After Riker's compaints of fatigue, Geordi's VISOR causing him problems,
and Worf feeling unusually jumpy, it becomes apparent that an external
influence is responsible. Counselor Troi investigates and finds that several
crew members have complained of similar symptoms stemming from unsettling
dreams. Gradually, using a holodeck recreation of the dream environment
programmed by those suffering the unusual effects, a mysterious string of
experiments conducted by aliens from within the physical domain of subspace
is dicsovered. As more incidents occur, with the crew powerless to stop them,
the experiments become more deadly. Riker, who has been frequently
experimented upon by the aliens, volunteers to take part in an experiment of
the crew's own to see if the intrusions can be halted.


