@Node TNG157 "STCCG.guide/Episodes/TNG/Gambit, Part II"

  @{b}Gambit, Part II@{ub}

Riker is accepted into Baran's outlaw fold by pretending to be an old enemy
of "Galen", and the mercenaries' mission continues. Picard discovers that
Baran's gang is not looking for Romulan artifacts, but for ancient Vulcan
artifacts. The Romulan mercenary Tallera reveals herself as an undercover
Vulcan security operative, and she earns Picard's trust enough for him to
reveal his own identity. A Klingon shuttle pilot carrying the last of three
vital artifacts is intercepted by the Enterprise, which becomes Baran's next
target. Riker is left for dead in the Enterprise by Picard to resume command,
as Picard leads a mutiny among the mercenaries and kills Baran. Picard must
try to play into Riker's hands without rousing the mercenaries' suspiscions -
or Tallera's.


