@Node TNG165 "STCCG.guide/Episodes/TNG/Homeward"

  @{b}Homeward@{ub}

Dr. Nikolai Rozhenko, Worf's human foster brother, has sent a distress call
from his hidden cultural observation post on Boral II, a planet whose
atmosphere is going to break down in less than two days. Worf beams down,
disguise as a Boralan, only to find that his brother has also been
masquerading as a native and providing them with means of survival based
on the technology of his obeservation post. Nikolai is admonished by Picard
for his severe violation of the Prime Directive, but when the planet is
within seconds of dying, commits an even greater breach by transporting a
handful of Boralans into a holodeck simulation of the shelter on their world.
The Enterprise crew - especially Worf - are now left with the dilemma of
relocating the simplistic Boralans to a new world without revealing the true
nature of their surroundings. Damage to the holdeck jeopardizes the mission.


