warrior, Worf grows worried that the boy will choose to shed all vestiges of
Klingon heritage. Visiting a Klingon outpost during a festival, Worf and
Alexander are cornered by a gang of street thugs. As Worf manages to fight
most of them off, the fight is ended by a Klingon who calls himself K'mtar,
a bodyguard appointed by Worf's brother Kurn. K'mtar reveals that the attack
was not random, but an assassination attempt planed by Lursa and B'Etor, who
are still scheming to someday overthrow the Empire. With the help of K'mtar,
and some gossip courtesy of Quark, the Enterprise sets off to track down the
Duras sisters when it becomes evident that someone is trying to tamper with
future affairs.


